#Xenic Poltergeist + Flayer Husk (#1085) - PARKED, engine bug confirmed.
#Animating an ATTACHED living weapon (husk mv1 -> should be a 1/1 creature,
#unattaching; its 0/0 germ dies) instead kills the HUSK ITSELF: probe shows
#the husk in the graveyard and only the poltergeist left on the battlefield.
#INVESTIGATED 2026-06-11 (deeper map): the husk dies 0/0/0 via
#afterDamage->destroy right after the poltergeist's StackAbility resolves -
#it is NOT the attachment SBA (unattach-on-animate + creature-exempt aura-SBA
#edits were tried and did not change the outcome; reverted as unproven).
#The granted newability[manacost/manacost] parses to APowerToughnessModifier
#whose grant-loop re-points (aNew->target/source = _target, AllAbilities
#~8300) LOOK correct, yet the +1/+1 never lands on the husk - the unattached
#millstone works, so husk->target=germ is load-bearing somewhere deeper
#(suspect: the leaf bound target=germ at parse via the head default, or the
#uynt ATransformerInstant deferred path). NEXT PROBE: trace addptbonus /
#APowerToughnessModifier::addToGame for the husk specifically.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
manapool:{1}
inplay:xenic poltergeist
hand:flayer husk
[PLAYER2]
[DO]
flayer husk
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
xenic poltergeist
flayer husk
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
[ASSERT]
FIRSTMAIN
[PLAYER1]
inplay:xenic poltergeist,flayer husk
tappedinplay:1
[PLAYER2]
[END]
